aria-describedby.description: Id of the HelpText that describes the ProgressBar.

aria-label.description: If not using a ProgressBarLabel, you can provide a custom `aria-label` to describe the ProgressBar.

aria-labelledby.description: If not using a ProgressBarLabel, you can use a custom label with `aria-labelledby` to describe the ProgressBar.

disabled.description: Sets the ProgressBar to an disabled state.

element.description: Overrides the default element name to apply unique styles with the Customization Provider.

formatOptions.description: Used to adjust how the numbers are rendered and interpreted. https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Intl/NumberFormat

hasError.description: Sets the ProgressBar to an error state.

id.description: Id of the ProgressBar. Used for the ProgressBarLabel's `htmlFor` prop.

isIndeterminate.description: Sets the ProgressBar to an indeterminate state.

value.description: The current value of the ProgressBar.

valueLabel.description: Screen reader only: used to describe the current value of the ProgressBar in plain text.

htmlFor.description: The id of the ProgressBarLabel's associated ProgressBar.

element.description: Overrides the default element name to apply unique styles with the Customization Provider.

valueLabel.description: Custom label text for the current value of the ProgressBar.
